======================================================================
CAUSAL STRUCTURE: ARC REVERSAL COMMUTATIVITY
======================================================================
  Two arc reversals COMMUTE iff their arcs share NO vertex.
  The non-commutativity graph = LINE GRAPH L(K_n)

  n=3: m=3 arcs, L(K_n) has 3 edges, 0 independent pairs
    Independent fraction: 0/3 = 0.0000
    Max commuting set: 1 (= maximum matching in K_n = floor(n/2))
    => Can simultaneously reverse 1 arcs without causal conflict

  n=4: m=6 arcs, L(K_n) has 12 edges, 3 independent pairs
    Independent fraction: 3/15 = 0.2000
    Max commuting set: 2 (= maximum matching in K_n = floor(n/2))
    => Can simultaneously reverse 2 arcs without causal conflict

  n=5: m=10 arcs, L(K_n) has 30 edges, 15 independent pairs
    Independent fraction: 15/45 = 0.3333
    Max commuting set: 2 (= maximum matching in K_n = floor(n/2))
    => Can simultaneously reverse 2 arcs without causal conflict

  n=6: m=15 arcs, L(K_n) has 60 edges, 45 independent pairs
